{"title": "First Offensive: The Marine Campaign for Guadalcanal", "description": "In the early summer of 1942, intelligence reports of the construction of a Japanese airfield near Lunga Point on Guadalcanal in the Solomon Islands triggered a demand for offensive action in the South Pacific.  Completion of the Guadalcanal airfield might signal the beginning of a renewed enemy advance to the south and an increased threat to the lifeline of American aid to New Zealand and Australia. On 23 July 1942, the Joint Chiefs of Staff (JCS) in Washington agreed that the line of communications in the South Pacific had to be secured. The Japanese advance had to be stopped. Thus, Operation Watchtower, the seizure of Guadalcanal came into being. - Summary by Henry I Shaw", "duration": 10203, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "16382", "name": "Henry I. Shaw, Jr."}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/first_offensive_guadalcanal_ab_2110_librivox/firstoffensive_2110.jpg", "copyright_year": "1992", "genres": ["War & Military"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Aaron Bennett"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Aaron Bennett"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ann Boulais"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "First Offensive: The Marine Campaign for Guadalcanal", "readers": [14238], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/first_offensive_guadalcanal_ab_2110_librivox/guadalcanal_01_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 586}, {"section": 2, "title": "SIDEBAR: General Alexander A. Vandegrift", "readers": [14238], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/first_offensive_guadalcanal_ab_2110_librivox/guadalcanal_02_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 297}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Landing and August Battles", "readers": [14238], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/first_offensive_guadalcanal_ab_2110_librivox/guadalcanal_03_shaw_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2235}, {"section": 4, "title": "SIDEBARS: First Marine Utili